  <section class="suds-home-faq-section" id="faq">
    <div class="suds-home-shell">
      <div class="suds-home-section-title suds-home-section-title--center">
        <h2>Questions Before You Book</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="suds-home-faq">
        <details><summary>What detail package should I choose?</summary><p>Choose Basic for maintained vehicles, Signature for most first bookings, and Elite for heavier buildup, pet use, rougher exterior feel, or resale prep.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you come to my home or office?</summary><p>Yes. Suds Auto Salon is mobile and details at homes, offices, and approved parking locations when access and route timing work.</p></details>
        <details><summary>How long does a detail take?</summary><p>Timing depends on vehicle size, condition, access, and add-ons. Elite takes longer than Basic because it is built for heavier condition.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do I need water or power available?</summary><p>Access needs depend on the location and service setup. Share parking and access details when booking so Sam can confirm what is needed.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Does detailing remove scratches?</summary><p>Cleaning, clay, and wax can improve gloss and feel. Actual scratch removal requires paint correction and should be quoted separately.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What if I have pet hair or heavy staining?</summary><p>Send photos before booking. Heavy pet hair, staining, odor, mold concerns, or unusual buildup may require more time or a different package.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Can I add ceramic coating?</summary><p>Yes. Ceramic coating is a protection upgrade and is best quoted after the paint condition and prep needs are reviewed.</p></details>
        <details><summary>How often should I detail my vehicle?</summary><p>Most daily drivers benefit from a proper reset first, then maintenance every month or two depending on use, parking, kids, pets, and commute.</p></details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="suds-home-final">
